==English==

===Etymology===
From [[w:James Granger|James Granger]], a 19th century English biographer.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈgreɪnʒərɪˌzeɪʃən/}}

===Alternative spellings===
*[[grangerization]] (mostly US)

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of [[illustrating]] a [[book]] with [[picture]]s taken from [[published]] sources, such as by [[clip]]ping them out for one's own use.
# A book [[illustrated]] by this process.

===Related terms===
*[[grangerise]] / [[grangerize]]

